p: Territory of Washington, County of Spokane}ss Arthur Powell on part Plaintiff vs. Defendant} In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, hold- ing terms at Cheney, Spo- kane County, in said Territory. To the sheriff of Spokane County, Greeting: In the name of the United States, You are hereby commanded to summon J.G. Brokey, N. Thomas, Wm martin, Louis Lee James Crandal G.N. gardner to be and appear before the District Court at the court house, in Cheney, in said County, on the fifth day of May A.D. 1885, at 9 o'clock, A.M. to there give evi- dence in the above entitled cause on the part of said by command of the court. Witnedd the Hon. George Turner, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal thereof affixed, this 1st day of May A.D. 1885 Kate W. Feauerbach, clerk By R. Strobach Deputy
